    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#jmr2012"/>, n. <citedRange>A.14</citedRange> (no image) </bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>62.1795.7</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>117300</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_πατρος"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F"><supplied reason="lost">π</supplied>ατρος</seg></name>                   
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_ιππος" type="patronymic"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F"><supplied reason="lost">ί</supplied>ππω</seg></name></persName></persName>                    
                    <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέθηκε</w> <space quantity="1" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">p</supplied>atros, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> fils de <supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>ppos a consacré <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">à telle divinité</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">p</supplied>atros, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> son of <supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>ppos dedicated <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">to such and such deity</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">p</supplied>atros, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> figlio di <supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>ppos ha dedicato <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">alla tale divinità</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>As Reynolds pointed out, the preserved letters at line 1 should not belong to the name of Demeter, because it cannot appear at the genitive case near
                the verbe 'dedicated'. So a personal name ending with -<foreign xml:lang="grc">πατρος</foreign> at the nominative is the most plausible.</p>
                <p>At line 2, -<foreign xml:lang="grc">ίππω</foreign> is surely a father's name. Reynolds suggested that it belonged to the name at line 1. If so,
                 line 3 could have only one name of deity, Demeter or rather the shorter Kore, in the lost part, but surely not both, as Reynolds thought it possible.</p>
          	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
